      "id": 361279,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Anethole, C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>12</sub>O, a major constituent of the oil of anise, has the <sup>1</sup>H NMR spectrum shown. On careful oxidation with Na<sub>2</sub>Cr<sub>2</sub>O<sub>7</sub>, anethole yields <i>p</i>-methoxybenzoic acid. What is the structure of anethole? Assign all peaks in the NMR spectrum, and account for the observed splitting patterns.</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcTRYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--63101273475613aee686626e8d7bf02f4d9ce1eb/OChem_18_EC_040.jpg\" alt=\"Proton N M R with shifts at 1.84 (doublet), 3.76 (singlet), 6.09 and 6.36 (multiplets), 6.82 and 7.23 (doublets). Relative areas are 3.00, 3.00, 1.00, 1.00, 2.00, 2.00 respectively.\">",
